==Abstract==

This IIP proposes a URI scheme for making INTcoin payments. It is adapted from BIP 21 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

A standard URI scheme enables:
* Clickable payment links in web pages and emails
* QR code encoding for mobile payments
* Application interoperability

==Specification==

===General Format===

<pre>
intcoin:<address>[?amount=<amount>][&label=<label>][&message=<message>]
</pre>

===Components===

'''address''': INTcoin address (Bech32m format, starting with int1, tint1, etc.)

'''amount''': Amount in INT (decimal, e.g., "1.5" for 1.5 INT)

'''label''': Label for the address (URL-encoded)

'''message''': Message describing the transaction (URL-encoded)

===Examples===

Simple payment:
<pre>
intcoin:int1qr7vy6sqrl8y22zl6rzw59v07e6r3k9unuwe3r9v2snz30swzaqw7wwd24y
</pre>

Payment with amount:
<pre>
intcoin:int1qr7vy6sqrl8y22zl6rzw59v07e6r3k9unuwe3r9v2snz30swzaqw7wwd24y?amount=10.5
</pre>

Payment with label and message:
<pre>
intcoin:int1qr7vy6sqrl8y22zl6rzw59v07e6r3k9unuwe3r9v2snz30swzaqw7wwd24y?amount=10.5&label=Donation&message=Thanks%20for%20your%20support
</pre>

===Testnet===

Testnet uses the same scheme with testnet addresses:
<pre>
intcoin:tint1q...
</pre>

===Extensions===

Additional query parameters MAY be added for future extensions. Unknown parameters SHOULD be ignored by wallets.

